name: WestJet Boeing 737-700 Economy Class Review! Calgary to Atlanta
description:
The Boeing 737-700 is the backbone of WestJet’s mainline fleet, with over 50 aircraft in service as of January this year.

They’re one of the most common aircraft in Canadian skies, and I’ve flown them a few times in the past, but I haven’t actually done a trip report on one, until now!

See what I thought of the WestJet 737-700 on this Economy Class flight from Calgary to Atlanta!

Thanks to Will and Robert for joining me on this great trip, go check them out:
https://www.instagram.com/willrdaviation
